title: NASA Statement on Nomination of Greg Autry for Agency CFO
description: The following is a statement from NASA acting Administrator Janet Petro regarding the nomination by President Donald Trump of Greg Autry on March 24 to serve as the agency’s chief financial officer (CFO): “The NASA CFO is responsible for executing more than $25 billion in agency funding across a variety of missions, including the Moon […]
author: Jennifer M. Dooren
categories: Office of the Chief Financial Officer (OCFO)

title: NASA Cloud Software Helps Companies Find their Place in Space
description: Planning space missions is a very involved process, ensuring orbits are lined up and spacecraft have enough fuel is imperative to the long-term survival of orbital assets. Continuum Space Systems Inc. of Pasadena, California, produces a cloud-based platform that gives mission planners everything they need to certify that their space resources can accomplish their goals.  […]
author: Andrew Wagner

title: Is our cosmos just a membrane on the edge of a far stranger reality?
description: String theory may be our best attempt at a theory of everything, except that it can't describe an expanding universe like ours. Now a radical new twist on the idea could finally fix that – but it requires us to completely reimagine reality

title: NASA has made the first radio telescope observations on the moon
description: The Odysseus spacecraft made a rough landing on the moon last year, toppling over and rendering much of its equipment unusable, but an onboard NASA radio telescope called ROLSES-1  was able to make some observations

title: "The monster will come for us all!” Mon Mothma rouses the rebels in new 'Andor' Season 2 trailer
description: The Death Star’s technological terror looms, and the Rebellion rises to meet the threat in this thrilling trailer for Andor Season 2.

title: 'Earth to Space' art festival set to launch at Kennedy Center this week
description: A nearly month-long mission is ready to lift off, with preparations being made at the Kennedy Center. To be clear, not NASA's Kennedy Space Center, but the Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts.

title: ‘Perfect space crop’: Australian company to attempt to grow first mushrooms in orbit
